A few things to be noted here, however we started with $AdS_3\times S^3$ system but we obtained the solution of $R_{t,y}\times S^3$. This might be because the DBI action we used is Nambu-Goto type and it can't solve the full system if the system have more than one curved subspaces. Similar kind of situation happend while probing F-string in I-brane (I-brane paper). If the whole system have more than one curved subspace then either we have to make one of the curved space flat by hand (as in I-brane case) or the equation of motion will make one of the curved space flat (as in this case). To get the solution of full system one should use Polyakov action in the case of F-string. As the Polyakov counter part of DBI action is not known one should not try to solve the full system with more than one curved subspace by probing D1-string. Rather, we should look at the subspaces with background fields which are consistent truncation of various string backgrounds.

